#: src/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.md:312
msgid ""
"In API documentation, the first line should be a single-line short sentence "
"providing a summary of the code. This line is used as a summary description "
"throughout Rustdoc’s output, so it’s a good idea to keep it short."
msgstr ""

#: src/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.md:316
msgid ""
"The summary line should be written in third person singular present "
"indicative form. Basically, this means write ‘Returns’ instead of ‘Return’."
msgstr ""

#: src/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.md:324
msgid ""
"All documentation for the standard library is standardized on American "
"English, with regards to spelling, grammar, and punctuation conventions. "
"Language changes over time, so this doesn’t mean that there is always a "
"correct answer to every grammar question, but there is often some kind of "
"formal consensus."
msgstr ""

#: src/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.md:329
msgid "Use line comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/1574-more-api-documentation-conventions.md:332
